No information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFFE6A41FA8894F8160FB83D" pageId="5" pageNumber="763" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFFE6A41FA8894F8160FB83D" blockId="5.[1394,2604,279,826]" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFFE6A41FA8894F818CFB9F0" bold="true" box="[1396,1743,673,706]" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFFE6A41F92694F8190EB9F0" box="[1754,1806,673,706]" country="Cameroon" name="North" pageId="5" pageNumber="763">Not</collectingRegion>
assessed on The [UCN Red List. The Dark Thick-thumbed Bat is known only from a single specimen. Further research is needed to provide a clear picture of the species’ conservation status.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
